text: nobody will understand how much this song means to me... i received a phone call at home that told me about my family‚Äôs debt and how its my fault as the eldest.. because i had no idea how much were in debt my parents never told me.. i was told that my parents would be imprisoned if i dont do anything.. there was a lot of verbal abuse in that call, after the conversation i had to go out at night.. i walked far away and sat somewhere. it was cold and i wanted to drown the noises with some music so i listened to exo songs on shuffle.. this song played first. it made me cry, but it was so comforting.. there was something about this song and suho‚Äôs voice that told me there was still hope in this messed up world... so thats why starry night will always have a special place in my heart. thank you suho ‚ù§Ô∏è

author: @dibakarghosh9674
text:
Hearing this for the first time. I heard "LETS LOVE" already. Actually at first I thought it was a single, like how DO and Xiumin had a single song out before going to military. Only thing day I knew it's mini album. I sort of knew, like cause then it's 'SELF PORTRAIT'. But I was not so like sure type of. This is my 1st song from this album other then let's love. I am an EXO-L from July, and there are so many songs, (specially ones which are not title track) by Exo, I have never heard. I have not yet watched the dramas. But than again I am 13 years now. I want them to be a part of my youth and entire life. I am still discovering so many new songs. So many songs to be known still now. 
So yeah this is my first song by suho as solo in his album, other then let's love (it has MV)
Hearing this today, feels so calming. Right now it's dark sky, hearing the word 'Staring Night' feels so good. What a perfect time. My first time hearing this and I am loving it so much......... live you suho. Come back from military safely dear. Our Uri leader.......We are waiting.
This song really,........I loved him hiring those high notes too. The entire song is really a masterpiece......love you SUHO
6:47pm
5th September 2020

author: @winteryouareneveralone9608
text:
The words Starry Night are really special to me. They hold endless memories from my youth. From the painting by Van Gogh being one of the first pieces of art I knew, to Don McLeans song Starry Night being one my favorite songs from my early childhood, so many special memories are kept with the words Starry Night. 
Now in my teenage days being a fan of Kim Junmyeon and all of EXO, with this amazing album Self Portrait, this song Stary Night is also one of my favourites. No matter how much older I grow, there is always going to be comfort with Starry Night.

text: I am really wondering why nobody watches these live sessions? Junmyeon worked hard and he blessed us with 6 live sessions of his album songs and some people didn't even click it once. Yes you don't have to like songs or you don't like these genres (they always have this excuse so) but if you are a fan, a supporter you could acknowledge that he prepared those and listen just once.I really don't care about numbers, i have no problem with that and i loved exo because i had always fun with their music, if i am having fun it is the most successful thing for me.But sometimes i feel sorry because i don't want members to think that their work doesn't appreciated.I don't want Junmyeon to think that his work less appreciated. Because it's not. I know  maybe Junmyeon is the last person in world to think that but everyone is human. I want him to feel special..

text: EXO are all so close yet so far from us. We feel like they are family and at the same time we treat them like they are living in another world. They were always down to earth, they didn't even once act snob to any of us or pretend we don't exist. Choosing this path was such a risky thing to do, they sacrified their youth, their personal life, everything just to make their dream come true. And they could just ignore us because we are just fans but they are treating us so nicely always, even when we don't deserve it. They are truly talented and I'm glad I got to know them, even 5 years after their debut, after so many sad and happy moments. I will be here. I will not forget the group that I grew older with. And someday, when I will be living on my own, being financelly stable, I will support them even more. Even if they give up, I will be here supporting them, from far away and giving them my heart and my time. They were all raised so well. They've taught us so much and we together keep learning things for each other. Because of their career, they couldn't really live like a normal kid in our age, but our young years, we can give them to them, we can share all our teen time and memories to make every emptiness they may feel, fade away. I have so much love for them inside my heart, the phrase "I LOVE YOU" is this and other 3994928 letters of millions of words. Junmyeon, Minseok, Yixing, Kyungsoo, Jongdae, Chanyeol, Baekhyun, Jongin and Sehun thank you for being our Suho, Xiumin, Lay, D.O, Chen, Chanyeol, Baekhyun, Kai and Sehun. Thank you for being our first loves and the people who made us feel like we can count on to somebody. Also, thank you for becoming EXO, having us, EXO-L, meet each other and make good relationships. Thank you for making us meet people all over the world. It is so special. EXO-L, thank you too, for being my sisters and brothers, for sharing your talents with me. You are the best 2nd family I could ever ask for. The purest people. I love you. I love you. we are one.
